---
import BasicPageLayout from '../layouts/BasicPageLayout.astro';
---
<BasicPageLayout 
	title="Accessibility | WhyA11y"
	description="Our accessibility statement explains how WhyA11y ensures our website is accessible to all users. Learn about our commitment to inclusive design and how to report accessibility issues."
	contentId="accessibility-content"
>
	<h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
	
	<section class="accessibility-intro">
		<p>
			WhyA11y is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. 
			We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the 
			relevant accessibility standards.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="accessibility-standards">
		<h2>Conformance Status</h2>
		<p>
			The WhyA11y website is designed to conform to the 
			<a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</a> 
			at the AA level. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible 
			for people with disabilities and more user-friendly for everyone.
		</p>
		<p>
			We also strive to meet the requirements of 
			<a href="/en301549">EN 301 549</a>, the European accessibility standard for 
			ICT products and services.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="accessibility-features">
		<h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
		<p>Our website includes the following accessibility features:</p>
		
		<h3>Navigation and Structure</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Skip Links:</strong> A "Skip to main content" link is available at the top of every page for keyboard users</li>
			<li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper heading structure (H1, H2, H3, etc.) and landmark regions</li>
			<li><strong>Breadcrumbs:</strong> Clear navigation path displayed on all pages except the homepage</li>
			<li><strong>Consistent Navigation:</strong> Main navigation menu is consistent across all pages</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Visual Design and Colors</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>High Contrast:</strong> All text meets WCAG AA contrast requirements (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
			<li><strong>Dark/Light Theme:</strong> Toggle between dark and light themes to suit your preference</li>
			<li><strong>Focus Indicators:</strong> Clear, visible focus indicators for keyboard navigation</li>
			<li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Website adapts to different screen sizes and orientations</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Content and Typography</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Readable Fonts:</strong> Atkinson Hyperlegible font family for improved readability</li>
			<li><strong>Scalable Text:</strong> Text can be resized up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
			<li><strong>Clear Language:</strong> Content is written in clear, simple language</li>
			<li><strong>Descriptive Links:</strong> Link text clearly indicates the destination</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Images and Media</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Alt Text:</strong> All meaningful images include descriptive alternative text</li>
			<li><strong>Decorative Images:</strong> Decorative images are marked with empty alt attributes</li>
			<li><strong>Explicit Dimensions:</strong> All images have width and height attributes to prevent layout shifts</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Code Examples</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Syntax Highlighting:</strong> Code blocks use high-contrast color schemes</li>
			<li><strong>Readable Code:</strong> Code examples are formatted for readability</li>
			<li><strong>Accessible Patterns:</strong> All code examples demonstrate accessible implementation patterns</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="keyboard-navigation">
		<h2>Keyboard Navigation</h2>
		<p>Our website can be navigated entirely using a keyboard:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Use <kbd>Tab</kbd> to move between interactive elements</li>
			<li>Use <kbd>Enter</kbd> or <kbd>Space</kbd> to activate buttons and links</li>
			<li>Use <kbd>Escape</kbd> to close any open dialogs or menus</li>
			<li>Use <kbd>Arrow keys</kbd> to navigate within components</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="assistive-technology">
		<h2>Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
		<p>Our website is compatible with:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver, TalkBack)</li>
			<li>Screen magnification software</li>
			<li>Voice recognition software</li>
			<li>Switch navigation devices</li>
			<li>High contrast mode settings</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="known-issues">
		<h2>Known Limitations</h2>
		<p>
			While we strive for comprehensive accessibility, we acknowledge that some areas 
			may have limitations. We are actively working to address any identified issues 
			and continuously improve our accessibility standards.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="feedback">
		<h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>
		<p>
			We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of the WhyA11y website. 
			If you experience accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, 
			please contact us:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@whya11y.com">hello@whya11y.com</a></li>
			<li><strong>Subject Line:</strong> "Accessibility Feedback"</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			Please include the following information in your message:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>The specific page or feature you're having trouble with</li>
			<li>A description of the accessibility barrier you encountered</li>
			<li>Your preferred method of contact for follow-up</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="continuous-improvement">
		<h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
		<p>
			Accessibility is an ongoing commitment. We regularly review and update our 
			website to ensure it remains accessible and compliant with current standards. 
			Our development process includes:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
			<li>User feedback integration</li>
			<li>Staff training on accessibility best practices</li>
			<li>Monitoring of accessibility standards and guidelines</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="last-updated">
		<h2>Last Updated</h2>
		<p>This accessibility statement was last updated on January 2025.</p>
	</section>
</BasicPageLayout> 